title: "Affiliate Disclosure - Contractor Software Hub"
description: "How we earn revenue and why it doesn't affect our recommendations."
---

<header class="bg-[#0f172a] text-white">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">How we earn revenue and why it doesn't affect our recommendations.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
  <section class="mb-12">
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">ContractorSoftwareHub earns affiliate commissions when you click through to a software product from this site and sign up for a paid plan. This is how we keep the site running without charging readers anything.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What this means in practice</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Some of the links on ContractorSoftwareHub are affiliate links. If you click one of these links and purchase a subscription or sign up for a service, we may receive a commission from the software company — at no additional cost to you.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Not every link is an affiliate link. We link to products we haven't partnered with when it's relevant to the reader. Our editorial coverage isn't limited to products that pay us commissions.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How affiliate relationships affect our reviews</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">They don't — or they shouldn't, and we work hard to make sure they don't. Our review process is the same regardless of whether we earn a commission on a product:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-3 ml-5 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-[#22c55e] font-bold mt-0.5">•</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700">We research pricing, features, and limitations the same way for every tool</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-[#22c55e] font-bold mt-0.5">•</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700">We read real user reviews from G2, Capterra, and trade forums to find patterns</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-[#22c55e] font-bold mt-0.5">•</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700">We include a clear "not for" section so you can disqualify tools that don't fit your operation</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The long-term model here requires honest recommendations. If we steer readers toward bad tools that don't deliver value, they stop trusting the reviews — and that breaks the whole thing. Our business incentive is to be accurate, not to be flattering.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Which products we have affiliate relationships with</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We have active affiliate relationships with the following software providers:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 ml-5 mb-6 text-gray-700">
      <li><strong>Jobber</strong> — Field service management</li>
      <li><strong>Housecall Pro</strong> — Field service management</li>
      <li><strong>Service Fusion</strong> — Field service management</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We are also in discussions with or have applied to several other field service and contractor software providers. Any commission relationship is disclosed on the article where the link appears. If you are unsure whether a link is affiliated, assume it might be — that is the safest assumption.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Questions</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">If you have questions about our affiliate relationships or want to know whether a specific link is affiliated, <a href="/contact/" class="text-[#0f172a] underline hover:text-[#22c55e]">use the contact page</a> and we'll answer directly.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-500 mt-4"><em>Last updated: March 3, 2026</em></p>
  </section>
</main>

